@node "Einleitung" "Introduction"
@next "(C), Vertrieb und Haftung"
@prev "Main"


   @{u}@{fg shine}Introduction@{uu}@{fg text}


 JSplit is a small tool for splitting and joining files.
 It has some great features like:

 - Fontsensitive GUI
 - It's small, fast and easy to use
 - It even runs with very few memory
 - Predefined splitsizes for often used disk formats
 - It's possible to get the splitsize directly from a device
 - Multi-volume Split and Join
 - Predifined name pattern for the splitted files
 - ...


   @{u}@{fg shine}Why I wrote JSplit@{uu}@{fg text}


 Some months before I often had to split long files because they should
 fit on normal disx (e.g. for sending them away).
 So I started looking for a tools that could do this for me and that
 could join the splitted files back together,too.
 In the PD-Pool and in the Net I couldn't find a program that did this
 in a comfortable way or they did need too much memory etc.
 So i started writing this tool...
@endnode

